-- FriendFinder Offers $210 Million for Playboy Enterprises
-- Bill Koenig
-- 2010-07-15T15:45:09Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-15/friendfinder-offers-210-million-for-playboy-enterprises.html

          
          
             FriendFinder Networks Inc. said it
has made a proposal to acquire Playboy Enterprises Inc. for $210
million, more than a bid by Hugh Hefner, founder of Playboy and
its namesake magazine.  
 Hefner, 84, this week said he wants to take Playboy
private, offering $5.50 apiece in cash for the Class A and Class
B shares he doesnâ€™t already own. That offer is valued at $123
million.  
 FriendFinder disclosed its bid in an e-mailed statement.-  
          
          


  
     
       
     
           
                            
                     
